availabilityZoneId.description: The unique and consistent identifier of the Availability Zone (AZ) that the mount target resides in.

availabilityZoneName.description: The name of the Availability Zone (AZ) that the mount target resides in.

dnsName.description: The DNS name for the EFS file system.

fileSystemArn.description: Amazon Resource Name of the file system.

fileSystemId.description: The ID of the file system for which the mount target is intended.

ipAddress.description:
The address (within the address range of the specified subnet) at
which the file system may be mounted via the mount target.

mountTargetDnsName.description: The DNS name for the given subnet/AZ per [documented convention](http://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/mounting-fs-mount-cmd-dns-name.html).

networkInterfaceId.description: The ID of the network interface that Amazon EFS created when it created the mount target.

ownerId.description: AWS account ID that owns the resource.

securityGroups.description:
A list of up to 5 VPC security group IDs (that must
be for the same VPC as subnet specified) in effect for the mount target.

subnetId.description: The ID of the subnet to add the mount target in.
